info.title: Rooch JSON-RPC
info.description: Rooch JSON-RPC API for interaction with rooch server.

methods.name: btc_broadcastTX
methods.description: Broadcast a Bitcoin transaction

methods.name: btc_queryInscriptions
methods.description: Query the Inscription via global index by Inscription filter

methods.name: btc_queryUTXOs
methods.description: Query the UTXO via global index by UTXO filter

methods.name: rooch_executeRawTransaction
methods.description: Send the signed transaction in bcs hex format This method blocks waiting for the transaction to be executed.

methods.name: rooch_executeViewFunction
methods.description: Execute a read-only function call The function do not change the state of Application

methods.name: rooch_getBalance
methods.description: get account balance by RoochAddress and CoinType

methods.name: rooch_getBalances
methods.description: get account balances by RoochAddress

methods.name: rooch_getEventsByEventHandle
methods.description: Get the events by event handle id

methods.name: rooch_getFieldStates
methods.description: Get Object Fields via ObjectID and field keys.

methods.name: rooch_getModuleABI
methods.description: get module ABI by module id

methods.name: rooch_getObjectStates
methods.description: Get object states by object id

methods.name: rooch_getStates
methods.description: Get the states by access_path If the StateOptions.decode is true, the state is decoded and the decoded value is returned in the response.

methods.name: rooch_listFieldStates
methods.description: List Object Fields via ObjectID.

methods.name: rooch_listStates
methods.description: List the states by access_path If the StateOptions.decode is true, the state is decoded and the decoded value is returned in the response.

methods.name: rooch_queryEvents
methods.description: Query the events indexer by event filter

methods.name: rooch_queryObjectStates
methods.description: Query the object states indexer by state filter

methods.name: rooch_queryTransactions
methods.description: Query the transactions indexer by transaction filter

methods.name: rooch_repairIndexer
methods.description: Repair indexer by sync from states

methods.name: rooch_sendRawTransaction
methods.description: Send the signed transaction in bcs hex format This method does not block waiting for the transaction to be executed.

methods.name: rooch_status
methods.description: Get the chain and service status

methods.name: rooch_syncStates
methods.description: Sync state change sets

anyOf.description: u64, u128, U256 is too large to be serialized in json so we use string to represent them

last_avail_block_number.description: The last available block number, may little behind the last block number. [0, last_avail_block_number] blocks were confirmed by DA backend. If meet error in background submitter job, it may be far behind the last block number.

last_avail_block_update_time.description: The last available block number updated time(Unix timestamp) If both of last_avail_block_number and last_avail_tx_order are not updated for a long time, it may indicate that the background submitter job is not working: 1. DA backends collapse 2. RoochStore is not consistent (cannot get tx from DB by tx order)

last_block_update_time.description: The last block number updated time(Unix timestamp in seconds) Should be closed to request time if there were new blocks. None if no blocks were received after server start.

last_tx_order.description: The last tx order in the last block
